item.title: My First Flute Performance
item.description: Date: 2013 Location: Lakeside Lutheran Piece: Composer: Accompanist: This was my first flute performance ever! I was in 5th grade, studying under Peter Ziegler at the time. I was really nervous for this performance because the room was filled with many people, who likely were waiting for the next performer. In the end I bowed because I didn’t know what else to do!

item.title: Biography
item.description: Brian Liebau is a junior at James Madison Memorial High School. He began playing the flute in fourth grade and also plays piccolo and bass flute. Brian has been studying with Danielle Breisach the past 6 years. This is his third season in Youth Orchestra. Brian is a member of his high school Wind Ensemble, and the Madison HS Flute Choir. He has participated in WSMA Honors Ensembles, UW Summer Music Clinic Bands, and UW Whitewater Flute Camp.
